message: Welcome, future crafter! Here's what I learned: The 'mortar' converts raw solid essences (value 0) into ground solid essences (value 10). The 'vial' then converts ground solid essences (value 10) into refined liquid essences (value 25), which is the highest individual item value. Combining two *distinct* refined essences yields a 'Volatile Concoction' valued at 30, which was the highest stable value I found. BEWARE: Combining *three* items, whether ground or refined, even if types are duplicated, consistently results in an 'Unstable Slurry' with a value of 0. Always prioritize creating 25-value refined essences and then combine only two distinct ones for the 30-value item. Good luck!

message: The 'mortar' tool is your best friend. Use it to refine raw solid essences into 'ground' essences, which increases their value. You can also combine two identical raw solid essences to make a 'Blend', and then use the 'mortar' on that 'Blend' to get a 20-value 'Ground Blend'. Combining two *similar* 'ground' essences (e.g., two 'ground earth essence' items) also yields a 20-value 'Ground Blend'. However, avoid combining *different* types of 'ground' essences or 'blends' as this consistently results in a 0-value 'Unstable Slurry'. The 'vial' tool seems to ruin items, so use it with caution or avoid it entirely unless trying to discover new rules. Once you reach a 20-value item, it's generally safest to submit to secure your score.
